This paper deals with the optimization of computer networks, specifically data center networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the balancing of functionality and security requirements, which is related to computer security (cs.CR). The use of linear optimization and probabilistic attack graphs involves mathematical modeling and optimization, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also introduces FASHION, a linear optimizer, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper specifically mentions data center networks, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
